description:
Best homemade pasta I've ever had!
It's only 2 blocks from my home and oh how lucky I am! Quick lunch, filling dinner, even fresh frozen pasta to cook at home - they've got it all.
My most favorite dishes (and I've tried all the vegetarian option on the menu, and off the menu) are:
Gnocchi with either Butter & Sage, or (off the menu) Cacio e Pepe (creamed Pecorino cheese and crashed pepper);
Vegetarian Lasagna (layers of softest noodles and perfect combo of veggies: zucchini, asparagus, bell peppers);
Vegetarian Piadina (flatbread sandwich with veggies "au gratin" and fresh Mozzarella);
Tagliatelle with Pesto (so much flavor, yet so tender);
Bufala Salad (a bit softer than Mozzarella, a bit less sweat than Burrata, yum).
Go try it for yourself! Buon appetito!
PS: if you go there for dinner, be ready to stand in line. But trust me - it's worth it!
